Title : Enok Palm
Text : '''Enok Johannes Palm''' (5 December 1924 – 31 August 2012) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] mathematician.

He was born in [[Kristiansand]]. He took the [[cand.real.]] degree in 1950 and the [[dr.philos.]] degree at the [[University of Oslo]] in 1954. He was a professor in mechanics at the [[Norwegian Institute of Technology]] from 1960 to 1963 and professor of applied mathematics at the University of Oslo until 1963 to 1994. He was a fellow of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] from 1959 and the [[Royal Norwegian Society of Sciences and Letters]] from 1961. He was decorated as a Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 1993.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Enok Palm|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Enok_Palm|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Enok Palm|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Bjørn|last=Gjevik|authorlink=Bjørn Gjevik|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Enok_Palm/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=75 år: Professor i anvendt matematikk: Kan tenke uten tall|last=Lippestad|first=Jenny|date=3 December 1999|work=Aftenposten|page=10|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Enok Johannes Palm 75 år 5. desember|date=12 November 1999|language=Norwegian|agency=Norwegian News Agency}}</ref>

